Top-Performing Hyperparameters¶

The top-performing combination of hyperparameters is as follows:

  • Regularization parameter 'C': 0.05
    • The regularization parameter C in the SVM model controls the trade-off between maximized margin and minimum misclassifed points.
    • C=0.05 -> priortize maximum margin and more misclassifed points
    • A value of C=0.05 suggests a moderate regularization strength, aiming to find a balance between fitting the training data well and generalizing to new, unseen data.



  • Kernel type: Linear
    • The Linear kernel is chosen, implying that the decision boundary will be a linear function of the input features.



  • Degree of the polynomial kernel: 2
    • In this case, the 'linear' kernel is chosen, therefore the degree parameter is not relevant.

Overall, with C=0.05, linear kernel, and degree=2, the model is configured to find a moderate decision boundary, capturing linear patterns in the data.
